I hope your advent season is going well. How are you preparing your heart for Jesus’ birth? Each little thing you do with love can be an extraordinary thing. 

“Serve God in the circumstances in which He places you” - St. Frances de Sales

Seeking Jesus right as I wake up has been such a life changing thing.

No phones, no screens until I’ve prayed and talked to Jesus first.

Changing perspective and thinking that He seeks us all the time, that the King of Kings is pursuing our hearts- it’s pretty amazing.

“I know you through and through. I know everything about you. They very hairs on your head I have numbered. Nothing in your life is unimportant to me.”

Jesus to Mother Teresa

Thank you x a million for all your support! I am finishing up some orders and then I can’t wait for Christmas!

This was a wood slice that I sent out last week. It’s one of my favorites!
Hi! How are you doing with Christmas coming up so soon? Know that God will take care of your heart! Prepare Him room this Christmas ❤️🎄
How are you preparing your hearts (and homes) for Christmas? Is there a place for Him to rest? Prepare Him room ❤️

As we get closer to Christmas, I’ve been reflecting a lot on St. Joseph. His leadership guiding Mary to Bethlehem, His own fiat to caring for Mary and Jesus.

We are called to love like Joseph. Give our own Fiat to the Lord.

How are you saying yes to the Lord?

This sticker was inspired by St. Joseph, the white lily.

Merry Christmas from the Tait family!

(Christmas in Polaroids)

We drove up to see our parents and siblings, then had our annual cousins’ Christmas party. We had lots of fun, lots of presents, lots of food, lots of karaoke, and took lots of pictures.

It’s been such an adventure. We’ve grown so much together. Always asking the Holy Family to guide us. 

Marriage is tough. It’s hard. This quote by JP2 sums it up really well. 

“Love between man and woman cannot be built without sacrifices and self-denial”

Marriage is hard, but it is SO worth it. 

Prayer to the Holy Family:

JESUS, Son of God and Son of Mary, bless our family. Graciously inspire in us the unity, peace, and mutual love that you found in Your own family in the little town of Nazareth.

MARY, Mother of Jesus and our Mother, nourish our family with your faith and your love. Keep us close to your Son, Jesus, in all our sorrows and joys.

JOSEPH, foster-father to Jesus, guardian and spouse of Mary, keep our family safe from harm. Help us in all times of discouragement or anxiety.

HOLY FAMILY OF NAZARETH, make our family one with you. Help us to be instruments of peace. Grant that love, strengthened by grace, may prove mightier than all the weaknesses and trials through which our families sometimes pass. May we always have God at the center of our hearts and homes until we are all one family, happy and at peace in our true home with you. Amen.

Happy new year!

It’s a great time to start new, start something new. 

First step to starting something new?

Ask God for guidance!

He delights in you. In your heart, your life, your presence. He’s trying to pursue your heart. I’m what ways is He showing His love today?

It’s been a while, friends! I hope you are all doing well. I’m still trying to get back into a routine from the holidays — plus my birthday is TOMORROW so I’m also feeling like we can go back to “normal” after that 🤣

Know that I am praying for you!

It’s hard to be at peace about the future, especially when you’re unsure about what’s to come. 

But God knows. And He will give us the grace to persevere

Anyone else feel like they are going through a storm in their life right now?

You are not alone. Put your trust in Jesus and He will calm the storm.

“Be great in little things” - St. Francis Xavier

This spot is where we do the majority of our “work.”

It’s where I do all my painting, creating. Where our kids do their school work, where some zoom meetings take place. 

This has grown to be one of my favorites spots. It’s not a big one. It’s a small desk area, with a foldable chair. I love looking at the saints and getting inspired by their stories.

And it’s in the little things where we can be great. Where we can meet God in (sometimes) the quiet moments and hear His voice.
I’m dreaming of adding some prints to my shop and this one is one of them. I can see this in a nursery or in a cute little office space. What do you think?

How do you stay rooted in Jesus?

What are some little ways that you give your day to Him?

We normally do our family rosary at night and when the kids are asleep, that’s when I have some quiet time for myself and with God. 

And lately we’ve been shutting off the tv more often and read the kids’ bible or saint books. I used to only read them for bedtime, but it’s become a thing where I say throughout the day, “grab a saint story!” or “grab your bible!” and we just read about our faith. 

It’s become such a special time with my kids, I love it.

I paint, draw, write, doodle in my bible and I just started putting stickers along with it and I love it because it adds a different element and look to it! I love my highlighters and markers, but sometimes they bleed through. Having stickers helps nicely because they don’t!

Do you like putting stickers in your journaling bible?

For whatever you are doing for your prayer, fasting, and almsgiving, this is a reminder that even the smallest thing you do can be for God’s glory 💜

I’ve been so worried about what I’m doing for lent that not focusing on the why. 

It’s so easy to get lost in a list of what you’re going to do, trying to figure out how you’re going to make it a priority in your routine…

I’m reading the Bible every day. Not on my phone, but my physical Bible. I’m taking out my highlighters and pens and just praying creatively however the Holy Spirit leads. 

Being a mom and wife, a lot of the time my creativity goes into what crafts or games the kids will be engaged in. Or what to cook for dinner that sounds good that everyone would enjoy. 

This lent I’m asking the Lord to create in me. To “create in me a clean heart.”

I can’t wait to see how this will go 💜

Let’s do some bible journaling ✨

I’m working on my drawing skills, so try not to laugh at my heart too much 😂

The Lord knows our hearts so well. More than we know ourselves. He sees all the bad, ugly, brokenness — and He loves all of you. Let Him chisel away and make you new.

“For the Lord sees not as man sees: man looks on the outward appearance, but the Lord looks on the heart.”

1 Samuel 16:7

Even if you feel far away from Him, He’s not. He’s always there waiting for you to call out to Him. Because He is good and loving. 

How are you calling out to Him today?

“The Lord is near to all who call upon him”
-Psalm 145:18
I painted this notebook for a sweet friend for her wedding guest book. And I love how it turned out! I wrote their names on the front and a bible verse on the back. 💜

Taitortot #4 is due in July!

It’s been a whirlwind the past couple months. We are overjoyed! Baby and I are doing well. The morning/day sickness is slowly going away so I’m praising God for that. We’ve been praying for a baby for months and finally after asking for JP2 and Padre Pio’s intercession and a few other friends to pray with us, it happened! God is so, so good.

Here’s how life has been lately:
The kids are so excited about the new baby. Whenever they want to touch my belly, they rub their hands together because they know I don’t like it when their hands are cold 🤣

I forget how big my bump is until I’m doing the dishes or switching the laundry

Not really weird cravings, but my love for veggie trays have been really strong 🤪

Please keep us in your prayers!

This Sunday is Divine Mercy Sunday. 

St. John Paul II said, “It is a time where we are blessed with divine mercy as it reaches us through the heart of Christ crucified”

I drew this bouquet, inspired by the Divine Mercy Image. I wanted this bouquet to look like it was bursting, overflowing with flowers, with beauty. 

I wanted it to represent Jesus’ heart. How it bursts with love and mercy. He longs to give it. 

On the back will be this prayer on it as a little reminder of His mercy.

Don’t be afraid to ask for forgiveness and mercy from Jesus. He’s gives it to anyone that asks. ❤️💙

This print will be available Sunday! ✨

Do you like it?! Let me know in the comments 👇

The Mercy print will be available on Sunday!

Can’t wait for you to have these in your homes.
Let it be a reminder that Jesus’ mercy is for everyone at all times

As I was flipping through the Diary of St. Faustina, this quote that I highlighted years ago caught my eye. The more we learn about Jesus’ mercy, the more we realize how broken we are and in need of it.

Last night, during confession, Father said to me, “the Lord is generous His mercy. Be generous with your mercy to others.”

I want so much for Jesus to give me His mercy, but how about me? How am I with others? I struggle so much with that.

So happy Divine Mercy Sunday. May God bless you abundantly and show you His mercy always.

St. Faustina, pray for us!

“Today the Lord’s gaze shot through me suddenly, like lightning. At once, I came to know the tiniest specks in my soul, and knowing the depths of my misery, I fell to my knees and begged the Lord’s pardon, and with great trust I immersed myself in His infinite mercy. Such knowledge does not depress me nor keep me away from the Lord, but rather it arouses in my soul greater love and boundless trust. The repentance of my heart is linked to love. These extraordinary flashes from the Lord educate my soul. O sweet rays of God, enlighten me to the most secret depth, for I want to arrive at the greatest purity of heart and soul.”

Diary 852
Keep praying and trusting in God. ❤️ I hope your week is going well, friends.

This Begin Again bible design. It’s based on the quote from Mother Teresa that said, “Do not let the past disturb you, just leave everything in the Sacred Heart and begin again with joy.”

I love it so much. We can feel overwhelmed with our burdens. But Jesus takes everything and takes of it and us. ❤️

Yesterday I went to a spring boutique and it was so fun! I got to meet new people, see some old friends, and share about our catholic faith. 

I had my family with me some of the time and I felt it was a great way to evangelize as well. My kids know that “mommy’s working” and love that they can be a part of it! ❤️

Do you often feel so stressed and anxious about what’s going to happen?

Here’s a simple prayer to help:
“Your will not mine”

When we let go of that burden of the “what ifs” and trust that Jesus will take care of it, there is a huge relief off our shoulders and more space in our hearts to love. 

I made these keychains as a cute reminder to do that! I hope these bring you joy 🤎

Journaling in my bible is so fun! I can be creative with my prayer and it’s been great.

Are you creative in your prayer time?

“Do not be discouraged for the Lord your God will be with you” Joshua 1:9
Some inspiration for your Monday! ❤️

“Do not let the past disturb you. Leave everything in the Sacred Heart of Jesus and begin again with joy.”

– St. Teresa of Calcutta

I love love love this quote. It’s one of the ones that I want to letter on everything. It’s so hard to not look at the past and feel a heap of emotions, especially if you feel a lot of regret, shame, resentment. 

But God renews. Each day He pours out ahis mercy and you can start anew. We can begin again with joy. Because God doesn’t hold things against us. ❤️

As a mother, one thing that has changed drastically over the years has been my prayer life. 

Seven years ago I never thought that my prayer time would consist of constantly being interrupted from trying to read and reflect on scripture or that I would be answering the question, “how many are left?” nonstop during the rosary. 

Those are the things I cherish now. Yes, my life is different than it was, but these little humans made life clearer for me. 

It’s not about perfection, it’s about consistency. But prayer is where everything starts. Even if I pick up my pen to journal and get a couple words down, that’s okay. If I read a line in the Bible and one word sticks out, that was worth it.

God sees it all. He looks at your heart. And He knows you. ❤️

For those needing motivation this week. 

You are strong. You are brave. You are courageous. He will guide you in whatever struggles you have and you will get through it.

How are you seeking Him today?

I know our days can be filled with so many things. It’s non stop. Then we seek rest. But are we seeking Him in our day and in our rest?

I felt this way today. It’s been non stop today, especially since my little ones are sick. I had a few minutes to sit so I grabbed my Bible and started flipping through it. This verse is exactly what I needed to hear. 

“Let the hearts of those who seek the Lord rejoice” ❤️

Happy feast day of Our Lady of Fatima ☀️ 

We’ve had a devotion to Our Lady of Fatima for a while. If you haven’t heard the story of the apparition and the Miracle of Sun, it’s amazing! It’s one of my kids’ favorite apparitions of Mary to talk about and one of the reasons we started praying the rosary every night as a family. Each one of our kids asks each of the children that our lady appeared to, to pray for them each night.

Saint Lucia, Saint Francisco, and Saint Jacinta. 

I was reflecting on the story this morning and was thinking how beautiful that Our Blessed Mother appears to the little ones. Children are so joyful, loving, forgiving. They want to know everything and most of the time with such joy and love. 

May we continue to have hearts like a child and faith bursting with curiosity of the love of Jesus. 

Our lady of Fatima, St. Lucia, St. Francisco, and St. Jacinta,
Pray for us!

Do you go to Eucharist Adoration often? If you do, what are your favorite ways of praying in front of the Blessed Sacrament?

If you don’t go often, what are some ways to help you go more?

One of my favorite ways to pray in adoration is journaling. I do it often, but when I bring my thoughts and prayers and journal during adoration, it’s special. It’s me and Jesus. 

And those times when I know I need something to guide me during prayer, I bring a book. Sometimes lots of books 😂

If you are wanting to learn more or be inspired, Ave Maria Press has a new podcast series called “Ave Explores: The Eucharist.” It talks about how we can live out our lives as Eucharist people and how the Eucharist can change our lives.

I think this quote by St. John Vianney captures our time in adoration perfectly. 

“When we are before the Blessed Sacrament, instead of looking about us, let us shut our eyes and open our hearts; and the good God will open his. We will go to him, and he will come to us, the one to give, and the other to receive. It will be like a breath passing from one to the other. What delight we find in forgetting ourselves that we may seek God.”
St. John Vianney

This prayer is one of my favorites. It is so hard to abandon myself to His will. I am working on letting go of control and trusting in God’s plan. 

How about you? Are you working on letting go of control?

“Father,  I abandon myself into your hands;  do with me what you will.  Whatever you may do, I thank you:  I am ready for all, I accept all.
Let only your will be done in me,  and in all your creatures - I wish no more than this, O Lord.
Into your hands I commend my soul:  I offer it to you with all the love of my heart,  for I love you, Lord, and so need to give myself,  to surrender myself into your hands without reserve,  and with boundless confidence,  for you are my Father.”

-Charles de Foucauld

“Cast all your anxiety upon him because he cares for you”
1 Peter 5:7

After one of the time Peter answers Jesus’ question, “do you love me,” one of Jesus’ responses is:

“Tend my sheep”

When we say we love someone, we lay down our life for them. We will the good of the other and lead them to do good things. 

When we choose to love Jesus, we know that He lays down His life for us. Will we do that for him and others?
I hope your week is going well! God’s got this. Give all your worries to Him and He will take care of you 🤍

✨Bible journaling tip ✨
Use your highlighters/markers first, then draw lines for your flowers and leaves. That way your pen won’t bleed if you color on it with your highlighter. I also like the look of it rather that drawing the lines first.

All these things live and remain forever;     each creature is preserved to meet a particular need
All things come in pairs, one opposite the other,     and he has made nothing incomplete.
Each supplements the virtues of the other.     Who could ever tire of seeing his glory”
Sirach 42:22:25

I really love these pinks and oranges. Do you?? I’ll be adding this as a print in my shop soon 😍 Happy Friday, friends!

I have told you this so that my joy may be in you and your joy may be complete”
-John 15:9

Praying with kids is hard. I’m sure you had to change the way you prayed before having kids. I know I did. 

I could no longer sit alone in quiet for longer periods of time. My reading interrupted, losing my page constantly. 

But we learn to adapt. We learn different ways to pray. 

I planned to take the kids with me to pray together. I knew it wasn’t going to be easy, but I kept in mind, that what mattered was that we got out of the house and tried.

We did it. 

It wasn’t easy. But God doesn’t want perfection. He wants us to make the choice to love Him. To make that time for Him. 

How has your prayer time changed since having kids?

I’m hoping to make this a consistent thing. Pray for us!

When the world is telling you to, “do more!”
God is telling you to, “Be still. And know that I am God.”

Only He can give you rest. 

I pray in your busy day today you are able to see God and find rest and refuge in Him from all the chaos.
